Folks,

I would be interested in any accounts or insights into what caused Digital to
cancel the 36-bit successor to the KL10 processor.  This was announced in May
1983 at Spring DECUS.  At the time, I was a senior software specialist with
Digital and the primary -10 guy for the Pittsburgh office.  I also supported a
lot of VAX/VMS systems as well.  I worked for Digital Software Services from
1980-85.

I am specifically interested in:

- the primary cause of the cancellation (technical or business basis, or both?)
- any discussions or debates over the decision within LCG
- estimates of impact to existing customers made before the decision
- actual fallout from the decision (what customers were lost as a result)

